-- Grundfos Buys Water-Treatment Company Isia as Pump Maker Expands
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-09-30T14:01:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-30/grundfos-buys-water-treatment-company-isia-as-pump-maker-expands.html
Grundfos Holding A/S, the largest
maker of circulator pumps, purchased Isia, which uses chlorine
dioxide as an oxidant and biofouling controller to disinfect
water for industries, utilities and drinking supplies.  Isia is a  Venice , Italy-based firm specializing in water-treatment applications featuring industrial plant-process
controls and automation, Grundfos and Isia said today in a joint
statement. No terms of the acquisition were given.  Closely held Grundfos, based in Bjerringbro,  Denmark , makes
more than 16 million pump units a year for heating and air-conditioning as well as centrifugal pumps for industry, water
supply and sewage companies, according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
